defaultSE ROCU defaultBUSINESS CASEdefault&#xa0;defaultThe vision for the South East 
defaultRegional
default Organised Crime and Counter Terrorism Command for the forces of Surrey, Sussex, Kent, Hampshire and Thames Valley Police is:
default&#xa0;
default“To create a cohesive regional response to serious organised crime aligned to the current South East Counter Terrorism unit.  Delivering enhanced interoperability and resilience across the region supporting all local Forces as well as national agencies and capabilities.”
default&#xa0;
defaultThe work to build a South East Regional
default 
defaultOrganised Crime Unit (SEROCU) is driven by a number of key factors including:- 
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultThe 
defaultnational 
defaultreview of Regional Organised Crime Units identified that there is not a consistent national network to link to national agencies, and presented a professional approach that seeks to define what functions, capacity and capability should be hosted within the regional structure.  It stated that it is never intended that the regional function provides for the entire requirement for the region and the host Forces; rather that the regional function provides the more specialist niche capability in a consistent manner that is both operationally and financially efficient.  
default&#xa0;
defaultThese 
defaultregional 
defaultfunctions are:
default&#xa0;
default1.
default              
defaultIntelligence – the regional intelligence unit
default2. 
default              
defaultConfidential intelligence – a confidential unit
default3. 
default              
defaultCovert policing – a collaborative approach to delivering and managing undercover operations and activity
default4.
default              
defaultFinancial investigation and asset recovery team – the regional asset recovery teams
default5. 
default              
defaultFraud investigation – the potential for the regional fraud investigation teams
default6. 
default              
defaultTechnical surveillance
default7. 
default              
defaultProtected persons/witness protection
default8. 
default              
defaultCyber crime and e-crime
default9. 
default              
defaultOperational Security
default10. 
default              
defaultGAIN – the 
default‘
defaultGovernment Agency Intelligence Network
default’
default11. 
default              
defaultPrison Intelligence
default12. 
default              
defaultOperational Investigative Teams
default&#xa0;
defaultThe 
defaultnational 
defaultreview of the ROCUs 
defaultalso 
defaultmade reference to the possible 
defaultsynergies and efficiencies with the counter terrorism (CT) infrastructure, in particular around issues such as sharing accommodation, sharing leadership, sharing back office support and at times sharing specialist assets. 
default It was recognised that the policing response to serious and organised crime is not the same as that required to tackle terrorism, and this position is based upon the day to day impact and the hugely diverse nature of the criminality – requiring an overall approach from neighbourhood policing upwards.
default&#xa0;
defaultWhilst the South East region has established a strong response to serious organised crime
default,
default the 
defaultprevious (pre-SE ROCU)
default arrangements 
defaultwe
defaultre inefficient due to their complexity and there are additional capabilities that can be included within the 
defaultnew 
defaultregional remit. 
