defaultSet Up Costsdefault&#xa0;
defaultThe cost of implementing this programme of work will be mainly staff opportunity costs.  
default&#xa0;
defaultThe Home Office is providing 
defaultfunding
default to support Regional Organised Crime Unit networks
default, including 
defaultadditional investment for the financial year 2013/14.  Th
defaultis
default 
defaultadditional 
defaultinvestment 
defaultfund
defaulting
default is available to strengthen the region’s resilience against organised crime.  Th
defaultis 
defaultHome Office investment
default will need to be matched locally by the same level of investment and commitment.  In many cases this 
defaultcan
default be met by redeploying existing operational resources rather than a call on new monetary resources.
default&#xa0;
defaultThe draft 2014/15 spending budget for the SE ROCU is £11.5m.  The source of funding for the Unit 
defaultto cover this level of planned spending 
defaultis 
default£8.2m contributions from the five forces and £3.3m from Government grants.
default&#xa0;
defaultPreviously,
default a lead force approach has been adopted for the current regional serious organised crime units 
defaultunder which 
defaultit was the lead force’s responsibility to provide business support to the unit.  A principle was agreed that the lead force for each of the units could charge 2% of the 
defaultunit 
defaultsalary costs to the other forces 
defaultto help cover the cost to the lead force of
default the provision of business support.
default&#xa0;
defaultThere is likely to be a cost implication of transferring con
defaulttrol of the agreed 
defaultSEROCU 
defaultunits to T
defaulthames 
defaultV
defaultalley 
defaultP
defaultolice
default. 
defaultThis will arise from increasing the business support functions in SE Counter Terrorism Unit (SECTU) to cope with the SOC assets. There will however be compensating savings for each force 
defaultby the removal of the 2% charge 
defaultcurrently 
defaultlevied by 
defaultthe four separate SE 
defaultlead 
defaultforces on 
defaultindividual unit 
defaultsalary costs. 
default&#xa0;
defaultIn setting up the South East Regional Organised Crime Units under a host force model it is assumed that the overall 
defaultbudget
default for the unit will remain the same (increasing in line with inflation).  However, the new, single, 
defaulthost f
defaultorce is responsible for all business support and administration, including HR, Finance, Procurement and Estates.  This will provide economies of scale compared to the 
defaultcurrent provision by four lead forces that will release cost savings and/or service productivity gains. 
default&#xa0;
defaultThe build of this 
defaultsingle 
defaultcommand 
defaultmodel 
defaultwill also provide an opportunity to revisit the current funding model for regional units and the provision of business support.
default  
defaultAccordingly, work is currently underway to produce the regional ‘Collaboration Finance Protocol and Principles’ 
default(to be incorporated into the S22A Agreement) 
defaultand a ‘Principles for a Cost Apportionment Model’ for approval and adoption for both this SE ROCU collaboration model and all other future SE Region collaborations.
